Package: openfacer
Type: Package
Title: A pacakge for the convenient analysis of OpenFace data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Davide", "Cannata", email = "d.cannata1@nuigalway.ie", role = c("aut", "cre")),
          person("Denis", "OHora", email = "denis.ohora@nuigalway.ie", role = "aut"),
          person("Sam", "Redfern", email = "sam.redfern@nuigalway.ie", role = "aut"))
BugReports: https://github.com/davidecannatanuig/openFaceR
Description: A tool aiming to help social scientists in using OpenFace.
    OpenFace is a state-of-the art tool intended for facial landmark detection, head pose estimation,  
    facial action unit recognition, and eye-gaze estimation.
    OpenfaceR provides summarising functions and a routine to transform openface outputs ito tidy dataframes.
    This package is developed at the National University of Galway (NUIG) in the context of a research
    funded by the Irish Research Council (IRC)
Depends: R (>= 3.5.3)
